==English==
===Etymology===
Named for [[w:Victor Grignard|François Auguste Victor Grignard]], a Nobel Prize-winning French chemist.

===Noun===
'''[[Grignard]] [[reaction]]'''
{{wikipedia}}
#{{chemistry}} The reaction of a [[Grignard reagent]] (an [[organo-]][[magnesium]] [[halide]]) with [[aldehyde]]s or [[ketone]]s to form [[secondary]] or [[tertiary]] [[alcohol]]s

